sections.heading: proposed by Legislature; election; returns; canvass
sections.text: Public notice that the proposed amendment or amendments to the Constitution of Nebraska are to be voted upon shall be given as provided in the Constitution. The judges and clerks of election shall make return to the county clerk or election commiss

sections.heading: constitutional, and it was the duty of state board of canvassers to canvass returns on constitutional amendments
sections.text: State ex rel. Oldham v. Dean, 84 Neb. 344, 121 N.W. 719 (1909).
